        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(claude-cli): surface re-auth hint when subprocess OAuth token expires",
        "body": "Fixes #97553\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `claude-cli/*` is the active model and Claude CLI's stored OAuth token has expired, the subprocess can fail with:\n\n```text\nFailed to authenticate. API Error: 401 Invalid authentication credentials\n```\n\nBefore this fix, that error was wrapped as a provider auth `FailoverError` and surfaced as generic provider-auth copy:\n\n```text\n⚠️ Authentication failed (provider returned HTTP 401). Your provider token may have expired — try the request again in a moment. If the failure persists, re-authenticate this provider.\n```\n\nThe user did not get the actionable Claude CLI re-login command.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nTwo branches intercepted the failure before the targeted OAuth-refresh handling could run:\n\n- `isOAuthRefreshFailureMessage` did not recognize the Claude CLI subprocess 401 shape.\n- `classifyProviderRequestError` handled the typed 401 `FailoverError` first, so the generic auth response won before the OAuth-refresh classifier could produce the targeted re-auth hint.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Recognize the Claude CLI subprocess 401 message as an OAuth refresh failure for `claude-cli`.\n- Route the auto-reply/fallback failure path through OAuth-refresh classification before the generic provider-auth classifier.\n- Emit the actual CLI re-login command for this provider shape:\n\n```text\nopenclaw models auth login --provider anthropic --method cli\n```\n\n## Evidence\n\nFocused local validation after the assertion follow-up:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/auth-profiles/oauth-refresh-failure.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts -- --run\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  220 passed (220)\n```\n\nFocused lint validation after the follow-up:\n\n```text\noxlint src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\n\n(no findings)\n```\n\nNew/updated tests cover:\n\n- Claude CLI subprocess 401 OAuth expiry is classified as a provider refresh failure.\n- Non-Claude-CLI 401s remain negative controls and continue through existing generic handling.\n- The full `runAgentTurnWithFallback` path with a real `FailoverError { reason: \"auth\", status: 401, provider: \"claude-cli\" }` surfaces the targeted re-auth hint using `openclaw models auth login --provider anthropic --method cli` instead of generic provider-auth text.\n\n## Security & Privacy\n\nNo secrets, credentials, or user data are read or written. The change only classifies an existing error shape and changes the recovery hint shown to the user.\n\n## Compatibility\n\nExisting OAuth refresh handling for other providers is unchanged. The Claude CLI guard requires the `claude-cli` provider context plus the subprocess 401 phrase, so unrelated provider 401 failures continue to use existing generic provider-auth handling.\n\n_AI-assisted (Claude Sonnet 4.6 + manual review and test validation)_\n",
        "branch": "fix/claude-cli-oauth-expiry-detection",
